comments: One of the most fun classes I\'ve ever taken. Everything was referenced back to the real world and all assignments keep you interested. Responsive and thorough teacher, would 100% recommend!
Excellent. Tuition well spent. Very helpful. Always available.

As someone who does graphic design on the side, and was only taking his web development class for the credit: BE WARNED! This is an awful awful and awkward teacher. He will let his failures as a teacher be the demise of your GPA

Areally good instructor. I didn\'t know anything about computer forensics but took the class for the science credit. Roos has patience and a way of checking to see if you got it before going on. He says "nobody left behind" and means it.
Great instructor. Knows his way around computer forensics and how to teach it. Will get back to you with an answer same day. I just wish Randy taught more classes than he does.
Interesting class. Good instructor. I really liked the hands on assignments and instructional movies. No suprises. Will take him again if I can

If your life isn\'t computer science...DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS for science credit!!! You will be floundering guarunteed by week 2 and have to drop the class. Not to mention the professor is nuttier than squirrel poo.
